Turkish Watchdog Ready to Fine TV Channels Over Programs, Sabah Reports

-- B y   S t e v e   B r y a n t
-- 
2011-10-04T05:02:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-04/turkish-watchdog-says-ready-to-fine-tv-programs-sabah-reports.html
Turkey ’s broadcasting watchdog said
it’s ready to fine or close channels that ignore warnings that
the programs they make are a threat to family values, Sabah
newspaper reported.  The Ankara-based regulator, known as RTUK, is watching
match-making television shows in particular, Chairman Davut
Dursun told the newspaper. The most important value is “the
family,” he said.  Click here for web link  To contact the reporter on this story:
